{"ts":"2026-06-12T22:47:21.538Z","author":"audit-quality-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-c90s"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"pm health 2.3-3.1s in dev repo (~2x the 1.3s baseline): drift-scan cache hit still reads + content-hashes every history stream"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Measured 2026-06-13 (warm, 3 runs): 2326/3076/2590ms vs 1.3s baseline from 2026-05-27 (PR#77). Sandbox health is 180ms, so this is corpus scaling: .agents/pm/history has 1222 streams / 22MB. CPU profile of pm health: ~200ms TOON decode (parseDelimitedValues 87ms + unescapeString 41ms + findClosingQuote 32ms + parseStringLiteral 24ms), hash update 96ms, buildIntegrityCheck self 93ms, 373ms async-IO idle. Root cause: src/core/history/drift-scan.ts (lines 113-115, 171-187) deliberately re-reads the FULL stream and recomputes a content hash even on a metadata cache hit (guard against metadata-stable replacement), so health is O(total history bytes) per run forever; the cache only skips chain replay, not read+hash. Options: trust mtime+ctime+size stat tuple without content re-hash; hash size+first/last 64KB; or make the full-content guard opt-in (pm health --deep). Relates: open auto-compact items reduce corpus size but do not fix the scaling shape."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["audit-2026-06-13","health","history","performance"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-12T22:47:21.538Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-12T22:47:21.538Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"audit-quality-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-y7sc"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"6588c6bc612fd19fe593b3fe260ee7b92c792b83440b4f88b2295798a7dde5ae","message":""}
{"ts":"2026-06-17T22:04:54.799Z","author":"codex-audit-20260618","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-17T22:04:54.799Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-06-17T22:04:54.799Z","author":"codex-audit-20260618","text":"Sub-agent performance audit evidence: current repo has 1293 history streams, 20691 entries, 24641681 bytes; hotspot remains src/core/history/drift-scan.ts full stream read/content_hash on metadata cache hits. Recommended safe shape: add cacheHitVerification mode, use stat-fingerprint for health warm-cache, keep history-repair --all on content-hash, bump drift cache version, and test health/validate/repair callers separately. Not bundled into GH-262/templates branch because it changes shared drift-scan correctness semantics."}]}],"before_hash":"6588c6bc612fd19fe593b3fe260ee7b92c792b83440b4f88b2295798a7dde5ae","after_hash":"d11368f6c50d64d027122fff7d0eb1defa15f57afd3fc8fbfc49dc7ac1fa2bb8"}
